    • enchant

      public void enchant(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item, int level)
      Enchants an ItemStack with the Enchantment. Obeys all conflicts and level caps. Use unsafeEnchant(ItemStack, int) to bypass. Note: This method is required to add CEnchantments to an ItemStack. Do not use ItemStack.addEnchantment(Enchantment, int)!
      Parameters:
      item - The ItemStack that will be enchanted.
      level - The level to enchant the ItemStack with.

    • unsafeEnchant

      public void unsafeEnchant(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item, int level)
      Forcefully enchants an ItemStack with the Enchantment. This method will ignore item and enchantment conflicts and enchantment level cap. Note: This method is required to add CEnchantments to an ItemStack. Do not use ItemStack.addEnchantment(Enchantment, int)!
      Parameters:
      item - The ItemStack that will be enchanted.
      level - The level to enchant the ItemStack with.

    • enchant

      public void enchant(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item, int level, boolean unsafe, boolean doEnchantEvent)
      Enchants an ItemStack with the Enchantment. Note: This method is required to add CEnchantments to an ItemStack. Do not use ItemStack.addEnchantment(Enchantment, int)!
      Parameters:
      item - The ItemStack that will be enchanted.
      level - The level to enchant the ItemStack with.
      unsafe - Whether to forcefully add the enchantment, or to obey conflicts and level cap.
      doEnchantEvent - If the enchantment consumer should be accepted when enchanting.

    • addConflicts

      public CEnchantment addConflicts(org.bukkit.enchantments.Enchantment... enchantments)
      Adds Enchantments that conflict with this enchantment. Vanilla Enchantment and CEnchantments can both be added as conflicts. If an item has a conflicting enchantment with this enchantment, the item will not be enchanted with this enchantment. This can be bypassed using unsafeEnchant(ItemStack, int)
      Parameters:
      enchantments - Enchantments to add that conflict with the enchantment.
      Returns:
      The CEnchantment instance.
